In interviews, many jurors said they believed some of the children were molested, but the prosecution never established that the defendants were responsible. This is a case I inherited, Reiner said. I tell my children all the time . Life is not fair, said Robert Curry, whose son attended the McMartin school. And some of the parents of children who attended the school blamed everybody. Afterward, the district attorney who filed the case criticized the current district attorney. In the nation's longest and costliest trial, Raymond Buckey and his mother, Peggy McMartin Buckey, were acquitted Thursday on 52 child molestation charges. 